HOUSE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 49
BY REPRESENTATIVE FISHER
HIGHER EDUCATION: Memorializes congress to include physical therapy as a
professional degree program for purposes of borrowing limits for students seeking
federal aid for postsecondary education
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To memorialize the United States Congress to take such actions as are necessary to include
3 the doctor of physical therapy degree within the definition of professional degree
4 programs eligible for enhanced federal student loan access.
5 WHEREAS, the legislature affirms that such designation is essential to enable
6 equitable access to advanced health professional education, particularly for students from
7 rural communities in Louisiana, to support the development and retention of a robust
8 physical therapy workforce necessary to address statewide and rural healthcare needs, to
9 mitigate escalating healthcare costs, and to strengthen statewide public health infrastructure
10 and long term workforce sustainability; and
11 WHEREAS, research shows that healthcare professionals educated locally are
12 significantly more likely to practice in the communities where they are trained; and
13 WHEREAS, restricting access to federal student loan funding for doctor of physical
14 therapy students would disproportionately affect Louisiana residents and further exacerbate
15 rural healthcare shortages.
16 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
17 memorialize the United States Congress to take such actions as are necessary to include the
18 doctor of physical therapy degree within the definition of professional degree programs
19 eligible for enhanced federal student loan access.
